The AI engineer's work involved a comprehensive effort to finalize the ICC BFC Connect application, rebranding it to ICC BFC-ITALIE. This included implementing new features like a notification system and enhancing existing ones such as Super Admin user management with password reset functionality. A significant portion of the work focused on rectifying role-based access control, especially for  and  to ensure multi-city, multi-department data visibility. The engineer also addressed critical bug fixes reported by the user, particularly login failures post-deployment and data inconsistencies between preview and deployed environments, leading to the creation of database initialization and URL verification scripts. The trajectory culminates with the engineer addressing discrepancies between preview and production URLs and the need for a post-deployment URL fix script.
</analysis>

<product_requirements>
The ICC BFC-ITALIE Connect application manages church engagement across multiple cities (e.g., Dijon). It supports a multi-role system: Super Admin (full control, user/city management, password reset), Pasteur (read-only, multi-city/department view), Superviseur des promos (manages own city's promotions), Superviseur Familles d'Impact (manages own city's FI sectors/families/members), Responsable de promos (manages assigned month's visitors), Responsable de Secteur (views FI/members in own sector), Pilote de FI (manages own FI members, marks Thursday presences), Accueil & Intégration (read-only visitors), and Public (self-registration).

Key features include user/visitor management, analytics with fidelisation rates (weekly/monthly/yearly from 2025-2030), and comprehensive city management. The Familles dImpact" feature uses a City > Sectors > Familles dImpact hierarchy for management and presence tracking. UI requirements include ICC BFC-ITALIE branding, dynamic ICC {City Name} Connect titles, a dedicated Accès Spécifiques login for Pasteur/Super Admin, and role/department-specific navigation. Notifications are required for Pilotes, Responsables de Secteur, and Superviseurs.
